cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is about artistic style transfer using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach that takes into consideration faithful representations of both color and luminance channels, which involves sophisticated training offline, suggesting that it may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple modalities to handle style and texture cues at multiple scales, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
